      • getMetadata

        public Map<String,Object> getMetadata()
        This returns a mutable map representing arbitrary metadata attached to this track. If the track was created through a File, a key of "file" will have a File object which represents the source of the audio. If the track was created through a URL, a key of "url" will have a URL object which represents the source of the audio.
        Returns:
        The metadata.

      • getTotalTrackTime

        public long getTotalTrackTime()
        This gets the total track time in milliseconds.
        Returns:
        The total track time. If -1, it is unknown at the time, else it should always be >= currentTrack time. NOTE: This value can change. If the track is able to continue playing past the original total track, the total track time will be updated.

      • isReady

        public boolean isReady()
        Description copied from interface: IAudioProvider
        This is called to determine whether the audio provider is ready to provide audio or not. When it is not ready, no audio data queries will be attempted.
        Specified by:
        isReady in interface IAudioProvider
        Returns:
        True if ready, false if otherwise.

      • provide

        public byte[] provide()
        Description copied from interface: IAudioProvider
        This is called to retrieve the actual audio data. This should attempt to return 20 ms of data. The audio must also respect the encoding type returned by IAudioProvider.getAudioEncodingType().
        Specified by:
        provide in interface IAudioProvider
        Returns:
        The audio data.

      • getChannels

        public int getChannels()
        Description copied from interface: IAudioProvider
        Gets the number of channels in this audio. NOTE: This only matters if IAudioProvider.getAudioEncodingType() does not return IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType.OPUS.
        Specified by:
        getChannels in interface IAudioProvider
        Returns:
        The number of channels. It returns 2 (stereo) by default.

      • getAudioEncodingType

        public IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType getAudioEncodingType()
        Description copied from interface: IAudioProvider
        This is called to determine the type of audio data provided by this provider. This determines how the audio data is processed.
        Specified by:
        getAudioEncodingType in interface IAudioProvider
        Returns:
        The audio encoding type. By default this returns IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType.PCM.
